I can't tolerate watching his juvenile shrieking for more than a few minutes at any one time. I've never been able to sit through an entire episode of his insipid "content". He's a disease to cinema, an imaginative, unwitty hack.

I'm very happy he made #1 here. Couldn't happen to a bigger, more deserving fraud.

And Alan Parker's "The Wall" is great. I've seen "The Nostalgia Critic's" anemic attempts at "cinema", he has balls of steel to come down hard on any film in the wake of his own pathetic artistic incompetence.

So glad to see him at #1 here. Great start to my day.
